# Indentation-aware config parser — conformance test

Tests `IndentContext`, `withIndent`, `sameIndent`, `block`, `line`, and
`parseLayoutWith` from `std/parsing/layout.ssc`.

## Imports

[Position, ParseError, ParseOk, ParseErr, Parser, PChar, PString, PRegex, PSatisfy, PSucceed, PFail, ParserContext, NoContext, PWithLocalContext, PReadContext](std/parsing/core.ssc)

[PSequence, PChoice, PMany, POpt, PMapped, PFlatMapped, PNamed, runParser](std/parsing/combinators.ssc)

[whitespace, whitespace1, identifier, integer, number, stringLit, skip, keyword, token](std/parsing/helpers.ssc)

[IndentContext, withIndent, sameIndent, deeperIndent, block, line, columnOf, PSameIndent, PDeeperIndent, runLayout, parseLayout, parseLayoutWith](std/parsing/layout.ssc)

## Config AST

```scalascript
// A config leaf: key = value
case class ConfigEntry(key: String, value: String)

// A config section: name { entries... }
case class ConfigSection(name: String, entries: List[Any])

// Top-level document: a list of sections or entries
case class ConfigDoc(items: List[Any])
```

## Parsers

```scalascript
// Horizontal whitespace only (spaces/tabs — not newlines).
val hspace: Parser[Any] = Parser.regex("[ \t]*")

// A bare value: everything up to end-of-line.
val bareValue: Parser[Any] = Parser.regex("[^\n]+").map(s => s.trim)

// key = value  (single line)
val configEntry: Parser[Any] =
  ((identifier <~ hspace <~ Parser.char('=') <~ hspace) ~ bareValue)
    .map(pair => ConfigEntry(pair._1.asInstanceOf[String], pair._2.asInstanceOf[String]))

// Skip blank lines and their newlines. Keep the repeated parser non-nullable:
// a single nullable regex can match the empty string before consuming blanks.
val blankLine: Parser[Any] = Parser.regex("[ \t]*\n")
val blankLines: Parser[Any] = blankLine.many()

// A section header: "[sectionName]" on its own line.
val sectionHeader: Parser[Any] =
  (Parser.char('[') ~> identifier <~ Parser.char(']'))
    .named("section header")

// A section: header followed by an indented block of entries.
// Entries must all start at column 3 (2-space indent).
val configSection: Parser[Any] =
  ((sectionHeader <~ Parser.regex("[ \t]*\n") <~ blankLines) ~
    configEntry.block.withIndent(3))
    .map(pair => ConfigSection(pair._1.asInstanceOf[String], pair._2.asInstanceOf[List[Any]]))

// Top-level: one or more sections or bare entries separated by blank lines.
val configDoc: Parser[Any] =
  (blankLines ~> ((configSection | configEntry) <~ blankLines).many1())
    .map(items => ConfigDoc(items.asInstanceOf[List[Any]]))
```

## Test inputs

```scalascript
val input1 = """
[database]
  host = localhost
  port = 5432
  name = mydb
"""

val input2 = """
[server]
  host = 0.0.0.0
  port = 8080

[database]
  host = db.internal
  port = 5432
"""
```

## Run tests

```scalascript
// Helper: pretty-print a config value.
def showConfig(v: Any): String =
  v match
    case ConfigEntry(k, vl)     => k + " = " + vl
    case ConfigSection(n, es)   => "[" + n + "] (" + es.length + " entries)"
    case ConfigDoc(items)       => "ConfigDoc(" + items.length + " items)"
    case _                      => v.toString

// Test 1 — single section
configDoc.parseLayoutWith(input1.trim, IndentContext.at(1)) match
  case ParseOk(doc, _, _) =>
    doc match
      case ConfigDoc(items) =>
        println("test1: " + items.length + " section(s)")
        items.foreach(s => println("  " + showConfig(s)))
  case ParseErr(e) =>
    println("test1 FAIL: " + e.message)

// Test 2 — two sections
configDoc.parseLayoutWith(input2.trim, IndentContext.at(1)) match
  case ParseOk(doc, _, _) =>
    doc match
      case ConfigDoc(items) =>
        println("test2: " + items.length + " section(s)")
        items.foreach(s => println("  " + showConfig(s)))
  case ParseErr(e) =>
    println("test2 FAIL: " + e.message)
```

## Expected output

```
test1: 1 section(s)
  [database] (3 entries)
test2: 2 section(s)
  [server] (2 entries)
  [database] (2 entries)
```
